parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall, jerk, or lurch, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of an accident.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or hesitates to accelerate
the transmission slips or jerks
the vehicle lurches forward or backward
the check engine light or wrench icon illuminates
and the vehicle may enter "limp mode" or fail to shift gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body can cause the vehicle to stall, hesitate, or surge, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of an accident.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or hesitates to accelerate
the throttle body sticks or fails to respond
the check engine light or wrench icon illuminates
and the vehicle may enter "limp mode" or fail to shift gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the vehicle to stall, hesitate, or surge, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of an accident.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
and the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or accelerate unexpectedly, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
the accelerator pedal sticks or feels soft
the vehicle jerks or lunges forward or backward
the engine RPM surges
and the vehicle makes a loud noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic throttle control can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or accelerate unexpectedly, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
the accelerator pedal sticks or feels soft
the vehicle jerks or lunges forward or backward
the engine RPM surges
and the vehicle makes a loud noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cruise control can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates unexpectedly while using cruise control
the vehicle surges or lunges forward
and the engine RPM increases.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off while driving, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The instrument cluster lights turn off
the vehicle stalls or shuts off while driving
the battery light comes on
the airbag light comes on
and the gauges malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can cause the driver to lose critical information about the vehicle's speed, fuel level, and engine performance, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The instrument cluster lights turn off
the speedometer
tachometer
and fuel gauge malfunction
and the warning lights come on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off while driving, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or shuts off while driving
the engine RPM fluctuates
and the vehicle lunges forward or backward.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air conditioning system can cause the vehicle to overheat, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The air conditioning system fails to cool
the refrigerant control valve fails
and the air conditioning unit blows hot air.
